reviewText:
Movie was good a little bit Corney but was delightful.
To see old movies like this of course seeing classic cars.
Is always exciting to look at and how far we have come in the automobile industry.
And classic movies is always interesting to look at also.
Dated but gives a glimpse of a much simpler time before they spoiled England
If you love vintage cars, a Scottish leading man,  and screwball comedy, "Fast Lady" will win your heart.
Julie Christie is beautiful! Good cars!
Fun movie that kept me laughing for over 55 years
I didn't like the feel of the movie, the acting was too fake, I could not watch it past 10 minutes.
Didn't finish it, I was bored.
Being from the UK and able to remember just a hint of the era of this film, it brought on nostalgia and some laughs. Definitely worth watching if you enjoy classic 60's Brit comedy.

J.Hannan and I (her husband) learned that this movie was created by the same team as their later "Those Magnificent Men In Their Flying Machines," long a favorite of ours.

It was quickly perceived that "The Fast Lady" fell far short of that film, but perhaps it may have had greater appeal to British audiences...
Goofy in a boring way.  Not the least bit funny although they tried to be.
I loved it !!! Recommend it highly AAA+++
